05936nam a22009495i 9783110939989DE-B159720211217065530.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211217t20121998gw     fo  d z      ger d  a97831109399897 a10.1515/97831109399892doi  a(DE-B1597)45524  a(OCoLC)979590779  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 ager  agwcDE 4aP23b.A37 1998eb 7aLIT0000002bisacsh04a801/.959221  aCB 49002rvk0(DE-625)rvk/17595:00aPhilologie und Philosophie :bBeiträge zur VII. Internationalen Fachtagung der Arbeitsgemeinschaft philosophischer Editionen (12.-14. März 1997 München) /chrsg. von Hans Gerhard Senger.  aReprint 2011 1aTübingen : bMax Niemeyer Verlag, c[2012] 4c©1998  a1 online resource (245 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aeditio / Beihefte ,x0939-5946 ;v110 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn den Beiträgen namhafter Editoren wird zum einen nach dem Verhältnis von Philologie und Philosophie gefragt: nach der Möglichkeit ihrer inneren Einheit, einer philologischen Erkenntnis und Wahrheit, kurz nach einer Philosophie der Philologie. Neben den editionstheoretischen, methodologischen und hermeneutischen Untersuchungen werden neuere Tendenzen der Editionstheorie und -praxis wie die Édition génétique und die New Philology diskutiert. Schließlich wird über die zunehmend wichtiger werdenden editionspraktischen und -pragmatischen Fragen wie Editionsförderung, elektronische Edition und damit zusammenhängende urheberrechtliche Fragen informiert.  aThese contributions by prominent editors inquire centrally into the relation between philology and philosophy, more specifically the possibility of an inner bond uniting them, of a philological form of knowledge and truth, in short of a philosophy of philology. Alongside studies on the theoretical, methodological and hermeneutic aspects of editing, attention is also given to recent tendencies in editing theory and practice such as édition génétique and New Philology. Finally readers are informed about increasingly important practical and pragmatic aspects of editing, including funding, electronic editing and the copyright issues posed by the latter.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCriticism, TextualvCongresses. 0aPhilologyvCongresses. 0aPhilosophyvCongresses. 4aEdition. 4aPhilologie. 4aPhilosophie. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aArndt, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBirus, Hendrik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEmery, Jr., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHenrichs, Norbert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacobs, Wilhelm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKempf, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLebrave, Jean-Louis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLessing, Hans-Ulrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMelichar, Ferdinand, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOtt, Tobias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOtt, Wilhelm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSandkühler, Hans Jörg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchepers, Heinrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScholtz, Gunter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSenger, Hans Gerhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSenger, Hans Gerhard, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStohlmann, Jürge